introduction.p: To pass an exam, you must complete a 10 additions table in 10 minutes at 70% accuracy, and each group of multiplications (or divisions) in 5 minutes each at 70% accuracy.
So, given the above, an abacus examination is supposed to take at most 30 minutes to be completed.
This is a collection of problem sets at each grade or kyu level. 1st kyu is the highly advanced and 8th kyu is beginner level.

subsection.title: Instructions
subsection.p: Complete each set of additions and subtractions, multiplications, and divisions as rapidly as possible while maintaining accuracy.
Check your answers with a calculator afterward. Rework any problems with mistakes.
